Here, σi, σss, σp, and σgs represent the intrinsic crystal, solid solution, precipitate strengthening, and grain size contributions, respectively. The precipitate strengthening component σp is typically expressed as the harmonic mean of contributions from dislocations shearing through shearable precipitates (particles) σFriedel and bowing between non-shearable precipitates σOrowan. The contribution from dislocation bowing can in the idealized case be described as: 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
